SIMPLE: presumptuous
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Presumptuous
<hw>Pre*sump"tu*ous</hw> <pr>(?; 135)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>praesumptuosus</ets>: cf. F. <ets>pr⟦eacute⟧somptueux</ets>, OF.
also <ets>presumptuous</ets>. See <er>Presumption</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Full of presumption; presuming; overconfident or
venturesome; audacious; rash; taking liberties unduly; arrogant;
insolent; <as>as, a <ex>presumptuous</ex> commander;
<ex>presumptuous</ex> conduct.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A class of <qex>presumptuous</qex> men, whom age has not made
cautious, nor adversity wise.</q> <rj><qau>Buckminster.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Founded on presumption; <as>as, a
<ex>presumptuous</ex> idea</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧False,
<xex>presumptuous</xex> hope.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Done with hold design, rash confidence, or in
violation of known duty; willful.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Keep back the servant
also from <xex>presumptuous</xex> sins.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Ps. xix.
13.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Overconfident; foolhardy; rash; presuming;
forward; arrogant; insolent.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Presumptuously</ent>⟦br⟧
